<HEADLINE> Khatami Hopes Iran-China Relations Further Develop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami here Tuesday expressed the hope that friendly and
cooperative relations between Iran and China would further
develop.
</P>
<P>
Accepting credentials presented by Sun Bigan, China's new
ambassador to Iran, Khatami said China enjoys an important status
in the world, and it occupies a special position in Iran's
foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
He said that both Iran and China are against hegemony and
power politics, are striving to develop themselves and their
economic cooperation has been going on very well. He said he hoped
for more economic and trade cooperation between the two sides in
the future.
</P>
<P>
The president pointed out that after the collapse of the Soviet
Union, a certain country has been trying to turn the world into a
uni-polar one, which he said is not realistic.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the proposed "dialog among civilizations" is
to enable every country in the world to respect each other and
treat each other equally, he said. Khatami put forward "dialog
among civilizations" soon after he took office in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Both Iran and China had in the past made important
contributions to human civilization and they can have excellent
dialog between them, Khatami added.
</P>
<P>
The new Chinese ambassador conveyed Khatami greetings from
Chinese President Jiang Zemin. He said Chinese government
treasures its friendship with Iran and is willing to strengthen
and develop its friendly and cooperative ties with Iran.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have strong economic reciprocity, thus giving
their cooperation a solid foundation and great prospects.
</P>
<P>
He said China and Iran have identical or similar views on many
important regional and international issues, and China appreciates
the proposal of "dialog among civilizations" put forward by the
Iranian president.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that Sino-Iranian relations will
further develop on the basis of equality, mutual respect for
sovereignty and territorial integrity, non-aggression,
non-interference in each other's internal affairs, and peaceful
co-existence.
</P>
<P>
Sun arrived in Iran on July 29 to take his new post. 
</P>
</TEXT>
