<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Unemployment Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus' unemployment rate in
the first six months of 1999 was 3.6 percent, Cyprus' Labour and
Social Insurance Minister Andreas Moushouttas said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus' unemployment in 1998 was 3.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the press after a meeting to review the latest
developments in employment, Moushouttas said the increase is
attributed to the recession in the manufacturing and construction
sectors as well as the illegal employment of foreigners.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, unemployment rate in the
construction sectors rose to 6.5 percent during the period.
</P>
<P>
Moushouttas noted that the island's prospective accession to
the European Union (EU) is likely to have a negative effect on
employment.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out, however, that the government is looking closely
at the issue and is already preparing necessary measures to
safeguard the rights of the working populations.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus started substantive accession negotiations with the EU
in November 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
