<HEADLINE> About 60 Percent Mozambicans Illiterate: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 31 (Xinhua) - Mozambique ranks one of the least
literate countries in the world with some 60 percent of its people
are illiterate despite government effort in promoting education in
the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican Education Minister Arnaldo Nhavoto said here on
Monday at a meeting of the Education Ministry's Coordination
Council, that about 70 percent of the illiterates are women.
He stressed, "we cannot realize our development ambitions with
such high illiteracy rates." 
</P>
