<HEADLINE> Arab League Chief Hails Sudan's Export of Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General
Esmat Abdel-Meguid on Tuesday hailed Sudan's landmark export of
oil as "a great economic achievement."
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid told reporters that he was satisfied to learn that
Sudan has exported the first shipment of crude oil in its history
and joined the club of the oil-exporting countries.
</P>
<P>
Sudan on Monday exported to Singapore its first consignment
consisting of 600,000 barrels of oil after more than two years of
efforts.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks, the chief of
the 22-nation pan-Arab forum expressed hope that the United
States-brokered Wye peace accord "would be implemented as soon as
possible."
</P>
<P>
The Wye accord signed last October requires Israel, among other
things, to pull back troops from another 11 percent of the West
Bank in the last two of the three-phased withdrawals and release
hundreds of Palestinians held in Israeli jails.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians and Israel are trying to reach an agreement
before Thursday on a timetable for the troop pullback and issues
related to the release of Palestinians for the two sides to sign
the agreement in Egypt during a visit by U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright. 
</P>
