referendum held Monday, saying it is a "very much encouraging
act", local press reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Foreign Ministry said in a statement that the Angolan
government, which supports the independence of the former
Portuguese colony, considers the free and just vote of the Timor
voters as "respecting the universally accepted principle of
popular consultation".
