and the United Nations is for the former Portuguese colony to
choose between special autonomy within Indonesia and independence.
</P>
<P>
East Timor, which was annexed by Indonesia in 1976, has been
seen to be a "non-self-governing" territory by the U.N. General
Assembly. 
