<HEADLINE> Rwanda Airlines Launches 1st Intercontinental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The private Rwanda Airlines, in
conjunction with Air Burundi, has launched its first
intercontinental flight of Kigali-Bujumbura-Brussels, the Rwanda
News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Managing Director of the Rwanda Airlines,Yewondwossen Mengistu,
was quoted as saying Tuesday that the once-a-week flight to
Brussels, Belgium, is a result of a joint venture by the two
sister airlines.
</P>
<P>
The Rwanda Airlines has also completed arrangements for weekly
cargo flight from Europe to Kigali using a leased B757 cargo
aircraft from Ethiopian Airlines for operations to begin in
mid-September 1999, said Mengistu.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda Airlines officials said that their company is committed
to providing services, creating employment, training Rwandan
nationals in the aviation sector, thereby providing avenue for
transfer of technology and contributing to the economy by way of
spill-over effect.
</P>
<P>
Mengistu explained that the company has a modest hanger at the
Kigali International Airport where minor routine maintenance is
performed. But major maintenance on aircraft is done abroad.
</P>
<P>
"As we grow, we want to build our own maintenance capacity and
preliminary discussions to that effect have been concluded with
the Ethiopian Airlines," said Mengistu.
</P>
<P>
The new flights to Brussels will be carried out by a leased
B757 cargo aircraft from Ethiopian Airlines on a three-month
renewable contract.
</P>
<P>
It is said that in the future, Rwanda Airlines will open
flights to Zambian capital Lusaka, Sudan, and Dubai of the United
Arab Emirates. 
</P>
