<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 166 Injured in New Quakes in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- One was killed and 166 others
injured in two earthquakes which hit western Turkey on Tuesday,
the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Bogazici Kandilli Observatory reported that the
5.2-magnitude earthquake, followed by another one of magnitude 4.6
rocked Izmit, about 110 kilometers east of Istanbul, the largest
city of Turkey, Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Officials in Kartal Hospital said that 18 persons, who were
injured during the quakes in Izmit, were taken for medical
treatment, but one of them died in the hospital.
</P>
<P>
They said that two persons were injured as they were squeezed
in buildings and others broke part of their bodies by jumping from
buildings during the quake.
</P>
<P>
Kocaeli (Izmit) Governor Memduh Oguz said that seven buildings,
which were damaged during the major quake two weeks ago, collapsed
and 70 persons were injured on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The main warehouses of Brissa tyre factory in Izmit collapsed
in the 5.2-magnitude quake, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
Izmit, also called Kocaeli province, was the epicenter of the
7.4-magnitude killer quake that hit western Turkey on August 17,
killing at least 14,000 people and injuring 27,000 others.
</P>
</TEXT>
