<HEADLINE> Smoking Ban Effective on Board Saudia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Smoking will no longer
be allowed from September 1 on board the flights of the
Saudi Arabian Airlines (Saudia) departing for and arriving from
the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) states.
</P>
<P>
The decision to ban smoking on board Saudia's GCC flights
was the first step to join other airways that prohibit
smoking on board.
</P>
<P>
The Saudia will next impose ban on smoking on board its
medium range international flights later this year, the Kuwait
News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Smoking is also banned on board the Saudia's domestic
flights.
</P>
<P>
Besides Saudi Arabia, the GCC, a regional political and
economic alliance, also comprises Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar
and the United Arab Emirates (UAE). 
</P>
