<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen people were killed and 13
others injured in two separate road accidents in Egypt on Tuesday,
the Middle East News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
A station wagon crashed head-on with a pickup truck on a desert
road,s south of Cairo, 11
people died and 10 others were injured when their van overturned
after crashing into a truck.
</P>
