<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Delicate Cells May Trigger Type I Diabetes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Researchers at Yale
University School of Medicine said that type I diabetes is
triggered by the body's immune system turning on delicate cells,
according to a report from Tuesday's Washington Post.
</P>
<P>
This finding, the researchers said, could lead to a vaccine
against the disease that affects more than one million Americans.
</P>
<P>
Susan Wong and colleagues at the University said they found
an antigen, a protein that stimulates an immune response, in
mice specially bred to develop what looks like human juvenile
diabetes.
</P>
<P>
Type I diabetes occurs when the immune system attacks the
pancreatic beta cells that produce insulin for the body. People
with type I diabetes do not produce enough insulin and must
carefully monitor their blood sugar levels and take insulin to
control them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0045 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Air Malawi Opens New Route to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Air Malawi has opened a
new route to Tanzania in a move to expand business.
</P>
<P>
The company's public relations officer Vera Ng' oma said that
the flights are arranged between Mzuzu in north Malawi and Mbeya
Region in southwest Tanzania every Tuesday and Thursday with a
12-seat Cessna Caravan.
</P>
<P>
The company's plane last week landed in Mbeya Region,
officially starting the cross-border flights, media reports said
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for Mbeya, a region bordering Malawi, to
connect with an international air circuit.
</P>
<P>
Ng' oma said passengers from Malawi and other southern African
countries proceeding to Dar es Salaam, Arusha and other
destinations in Tanzania, can take flights of a Tanzanian private
company Precision Air, under a special agreement signed between
the two airlines.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, passengers travelling to Malawi, South Africa and
Europe from Tanzania can take off from Mbeya Region, he said.
</P>
<P>
The public relations officer said that with the privatization
of the Mbeya Cement Company, and the opening of the Mtwara
Development Corridor, more and more people would book Air Malawi
flights between Mzuzu and Mbeya.
</P>
<P>
!0It took us almost an hour from Mzuzu to Mbeya and we had a
comfortable flight,!1 said a French tourist, Michael Dupuls, the
only passenger boarding the maiden flight.
</P>
<P>
The Precision Air service controller, Mwanga Misoke, said he
is optimistic that Air Malawi will boost business as well as
promoting interaction between the people of the two countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
