<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Residents in Burundi's capital
Bujumbura stored up food Tuesday in fear of further violence after
rebels killed 38 civilians at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The army deployed more troops around the capital following the
killing of 20 rebels in its repulsion.
</P>
<P>
Rebels attacked two suburbs of the city on Saturday night,
murdering 38 civilians including at least 12 children.
</P>
<P>
