Burundi' s civil war, an ethnic conflict between majority Hutus
and dominant Tutsis.
</P>
<P>
The weekend violence broke a calm that had largely returned to
Bujumbura since military leader Pierre Buyoya came to power in a
coup in July 1996, ousting a Hutu-led civilian government.
