<HEADLINE> Bulgaria to Cut Military by 50 Percent in Four Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria will make cuts in its
armed forces in four years, Defense Minister Georgi Ananiev said.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister announced Tuesday a package of reforms for
the military, saying the country will cut the military from its
current 93,000 to 45,000 personnel in four years.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country will also streamline the army's
equipment. Warplanes will be cut from 465 to 218 and tanks from 1,
500 to 750.
</P>
<P>
He said the aim of the reform package, which was submitted to
the government for approval, is to raise the army's combat
strength. 
