<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Announces 10 Percent Rise in Social Security Pensions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Social Security
System (SSS) Wednesday announced a 10 percent pension increase to
its 800,000 pensioners, Philippine News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made here during the 42nd anniversary
celebration of the major social security body in the nation.
</P>
<P>
The increase in social security pension for retirement,
disability and death is being made without need for additional
contributions or any increase in the rate of the contributions,
SSS Chairman Carlos Arellano said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the increase in pensions could not have been
possible were it not for the huge investment earnings.
</P>
<P>
The SSS investment earnings for the first six months of the
year amounted to 11.8 billion pesos (295 million U.S. dollars),
almost half of which came from equity investments.
</P>
<P>
Compared to last year's performance for the same period, this
year's investment income is higher by 43 percent, he added.
</P>
<P>
Arellano also said that its resources had grown to almost 170
billion pesos (4.25 billion dollars) as of this June through
better management of investments.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue to review our programs to see how we can
increase or enhance benefits from time to time," Arellano added.
</P>
