<HEADLINE> Silver, Gold Prices Up in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Both Silver and gold prices
recovered Wednesday on the bullion market in Mumbai (Bombay) on
fresh buying coupled with better overseas advice.
</P>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness) rose by 65 rupees (1.51 U.S.
dollars) to end at 8,075 rupees (187.79 U.S. dollars) per kilogram
from the last close of 8,010 rupees (186.28 U.S. dollars).
