<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) increased by 60 rupees (1.40 U.S.
dollars) to end at 7,950 rupees (184.88 U.S. dollars) per kg from
last close of 7,890 rupees (183.48 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, standard gold, which held steady for the last couple
of days, turned firm when it rose by 10 rupees (0.23 U.S. dollar)
to end at 4,060 rupees (94.42 U.S. dollars) per ten grams from the
last close of 4,050 rupees (94.19 U.S. dollars). 
