<HEADLINE> Thailand Ambitious in Training Own Astronauts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is ambitious to
develop more space projects, including the training of its own
astronautical personnel, the Thai News Agency quoted a senior
Science, Technology and Environment Ministry official as saying
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Science Minister Arthit Urairat will lead a group of Thai
delegates from agencies involving in astronautical affairs and
academics from local universities to attend an international space
conference, Suvit Viboonyagseth, the ministry's deputy permanent
secretary, said.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, to be held in New Delhi between November
15 and 20, the minister would propose that a regional remote
zoning branch be set up in Thailand to serve as a training center
for astronautical personnel, including those from Thailand, Suvit
said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand now has technical potential to develop its own
satellite and other space projects, despite inadequate personnel
and budget constraints which had undermined the efforts for
further development, Suvit said.
</P>
<P>
The planned regional remote zoning branch would then help the
country make a good debut for its own space development programs,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Bangkok is also planning to take part in a regional satellite
project to follow updated rice information from Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
