<HEADLINE> Cyprus Says Turkey Responsible for Murder of Greek </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Cypriot government
Wednesday held the Turkish occupation authorities in northern
Cyprus responsible for the murder of a Greek Cypriot.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Ioannis Kasoulides said that his
ministry would summon a representative of the United Nations
Peacekeeping Force in Cyprus (UNFICYP) regarding the murder.
</P>
<P>
Stelios Harpas, 69, from the Rizikarpaso village in northern
Cyprus was kidnapped and murdered on Monday night, reportedly by
two persons believed to be Turkish settlers.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Turkish Cypriots-controlled
north and the Greek Cypriots-dominated south since 1974 when
Turkish troops invaded and occupied the northern third of the
island in the wake of a failed coup seeking union with Athens.
</P>
<P>
Kasoulides said "the Cyprus government has an obligation to
state publicly that...the occupation authorities are responsible
for the safety of the enclaved (Greek Cypriots in northern
Cyprus)."
</P>
<P>
He said efforts had been made to bring the body to southern
Cyprus and carry out a post mortem examination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
