<HEADLINE> South Korea Wins Face-off Against Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUKUOKA, Japan, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Japan faced off South
Korea when the Qualifying round went into full wing at the current
Asian men's basketball championship on Wednesday as the South
Koreans stole away the win and set up a convenient posting in the
quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Point Guard Kang Dong-Hee made a crucial steal with one minute
left to post South Korea a 64-61 knockdown of Japan, who
squandered a six-point lead with 2:30 to go.
</P>
<P>
The ball-handler Kang, 33, initiated a final comeback by a
steal from back court following two 3-pointers including the one
nailed the net with 22 seconds remaining.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans turned two fast-breaks into four points to
snatch the key win, which almost insured a finals meeting with the
tournament favorites China.
</P>
<P>
"We played a good defense game," South Korea's head coach Shin
Sun-woo said. "The decided shots from two corners are the key
factor to win the game."
</P>
<P>
The fouled-out Seo Jang-Hoon led the Koreans with 19 points
with Kim and Cho contributing 13 and 10, respectively. Japan's
Hasegawa Makoto led the game with 20 points.
</P>
<P>
"We could have won the game, but we did not," Japan's head
coach Kohama Mototaka said. "I think my players did not take the
game as serious as I thought."
</P>
<P>
Japan could face China in the semi-finals if it beat Chinese
Taipei, who handled off Syria 89-81, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
China proved its overwhelming domination in group E in the
round-robin quarter-finals, ousting Saudi Arabia 85-56.
</P>
<P>
The expansion Chinese team had all its players on target with
pivot Wang Zhizhi led the squad with 12 points.
</P>
<P>
China fielded quite different teams in two halves to get all
players pop up for a potential semi-final crash against Japan and
final meeting with South Korea, the only matches that deserve
China's respects.
</P>
<P>
In the other quarter-final game, Lebanon surrendered to Kuwait
for its second loss of the competition, 86-81.
</P>
<P>
The United Arab Emirates outplayed Hong Kong of China 94-88,
Bahrain beat Malaysia 90-85, while Philippines overcame Thailand
82-58 in the classification playoffs. 
