<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Culture Week to Open in Paris (Part 2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Napoleon once said: "If China wakes, the sleeping lion will
shake the world."
</P>
<P>
Lying in his tomb about two kilometers away in the grandiose
golden-crowned Invalides Military Museum to the east, Napoleon
would be amused to know that a Chinese lion is gazing at him from
the garden of UNESCO 200 years later.
</P>
<P>
"This year, two noteworthy international activities
celebrating the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China will include the "China Culture Week - '99 Paris
" in coordination with UNESCO. The other is the Fortune 99 Forum
in Shanghai in coordination with Warner Brothers," said Zhao
Qizheng, director of the Information Office of the State Council
of China.
</P>
<P>
With a 320-man delegation and 40 containers of exhibition
goods, China intends to use Paris to let the French and other
Europeans gain a better understanding of the country, said Zhao.
</P>
<P>
Even before the festival opened, many guests were visiting
the hall, admiring the Peking opera costumes, the ceramics, wooden
and bamboo mini-sculptures, and the ancient classics in Chinese
medicine.
</P>
<P>
 "Heng mei (very beautiful), duo shao qian (How much)?" said a
Frenchman, who spoke a few words of Chinese, as he watched a
painter from Zhejiang province paint a fan with a picture of a
Chinese maiden sitting in a boat on the West Lake in Hangzhou,
longing perhaps for her boyfriend.
</P>
<P>
 One reason China chose Paris to hold this exhibition is
because France, among most Western countries, is culturally close
to China.
</P>
<P>
"The cultural level of French people is high. They understand
civilizations and admire the Chinese culture. Among many
foreigners, the French are more familiar with China's history and
traditions," said Ma Chengyuan.
</P>
<P>
"When President Chirac visited the Shanghai Museum he made a
speech saying that the Great Wall is history, the Great Canal is
history, and Pudong New Area in Shanghai is also history,'' said
Zhao Qizheng, a former vice mayor of Shanghai, who accompanied
Chirac during his tour of the Chinese metropolis in May.
</P>
<P>
 Shao Yudong, director of the press and information office
of Shanghai Pudong New Area, said that Pudong is trying to catch
up with the financial district of La Defense, located west of
Paris.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai municipal government has on display a model of
the financial district in the Pudong New Area, which is called, Lu
Jiazui, and it is one of the fastest developing zones in the Asia-
Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Japanese, U.S. and European investment, as well as many
investment projects from Hong Kong and Taiwan, are being made in
Lu Jiazui.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
