<HEADLINE> Information Sector Maintains Fast Growth in east China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The electronic information
industry in east China's Shandong Province has been enjoying fast-
growth momentum, with output values in the first seven months this
year topping 22.15 billion yuan, up 30 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
According to Sun Zhiheng, director of the Provincial Bureau of
Electronics Industry, the sector had sales incomes of 13.3 billion
yuan in the January-July period, also up 30 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The sector made a total profit of 500 million yuan in the same
period, a rise of 60 percent.
</P>
<P>
Sun noted that Shandong, an economic powerhouse in China's
coastal areas, has given priority to developing the export-
oriented electronic information sector as an industrial pillar.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, the province has set up 18
Sino-foreign joint ventures in the sector, and realized 190
million U.S. dollars from exports.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the province developed some 27 items of new
electronic information products through scientific research in the
first half of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
