<HEADLINE> Pakistan, India Exchange Fire on Disputed Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani and Indian troops
Wednesday exchanged fire across the Line of Control (LoC) in the
disputed area of Kashmir and a Pakistani woman was killed.
</P>
<P>
Indian troops unprovokedly fired across the LoC, killing a
woman and wounding three persons at Aathmuqam, according to an
army statement here.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani troops gave selective retaliation to the second
Indian violation at the LoC this week, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan claimed to have foiled an Indian attempt to capture a
strategic Pakistani post at Shyok-Tutrok sector early Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to defense experts, exchange of firing at the LoC
between the two countries used not to take place after mid-August
every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
