<HEADLINE> Bank Loan For Science Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Zhangjiang Model Base for
Technological Innovation, a major science park in east China's
Shanghai Municipality, has been granted a 500 million yuan
development loan by the Shanghai Branch of the Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China (ICBC).
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed here today, the bank offered the loan
and promised to further help development of the science park which
is home to hi-tech enterprises engaged in the pharmaceutical and
software industries.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Chinese banks have been busy signing cooperative
agreements with hi-tech companies, many of them run by
universities, in response to the government call to reinvigorate
the nation by the application of science and education.
</P>
<P>
China is now learning from developed nations and plans to
accelerate its pace of economic and social progress by boosting
the hi-tech sector.  
</P>
</TEXT>
