<HEADLINE> Office Building for Macao SAR Officials Put to Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The office building for leading
officials of the future Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR)
was put to use Wednesday without a formal unveiling ceremony.
</P>
<P>
About 50 office workers are ready to start work at the building,
according to Ho Veng On, who acts as a coordinator between the
office of the chief executive-designate of the Macao SAR and the
current Portuguese Macao government.
</P>
<P>
Ho noted that the leading officials of the Macao SAR will move
into the building successively in the coming days and that their
work will go on smoothly.
</P>
<P>
On August 11, the State Council of China announced the
appointment of eight leading SAR officials on the basis of
nomination by Edmund Ho Hau Wah, chief executive-designate of the
SAR.
</P>
<P>
Edmund Ho told reporters Tuesday that the building is only a
place for the leading officials to make preparations for their
future work, and it will not become a second power center, for the
Portuguese Macao government holds administrative power till
December 19.
</P>
<P>
Decoration of the building started at the end of June. The
expenses are defrayed by the central government of China and will
be repaid by the Macao SAR government after the latter's
establishment on December 20 this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
