<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Puts Emphasis on "Three Stresses" Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee, said today that the educating of
party officials in the "three stresses" must be carried out to the
letter.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the remarks while attending the opening ceremony of a
new semester of the Party School, of which he is also president.
</P>
<P>
The "three stresses" involves underlining and strengthening
theoretical study, political awareness, and good conduct.
</P>
<P>
"The education program has started well and should also end on
a high note," said Hu, who is also a member of the Secretariat of
the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The new education drive is considered an important measure
taken by the Party to improve its leadership and the quality of
Party officials.
</P>
<P>
Generally speaking, notable achievements have been made in the
"three stresses" education campaign, Hu said but added that there
is still a long way to go.
</P>
<P>
"Party leaders at all levels should improve their study of
Marxism, Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought, and particularly Deng
Xiaoping Theory, so as to sharpen their political consciousness,"
he commented.
</P>
<P>
He said the experiment carried out in a number of regions and
ministries has proved the effectiveness of the education campaign
in improving the leadership of the Party and working attitude of
cadres.
</P>
<P>
Hu urged Party committees and leaders at various levels to put
the education campaign at the top of their agenda, and take
concrete steps to improve their leadership and work standards.
</P>
<P>
The Party School welcomed 835 students in the second half of
this year, including cadres attending the training course for
minority Chinese affairs from Xinjiang and Tibet autonomous
regions, and cadres whose native home is Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Qinghong, an alternate member of the Political Bureau of
the CPC Central Committee, member of the Secretariat of the CPC
Central Committee, and head of the Organization Department of the
CPC Central Committee, was also present at the opening ceremony
today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
