<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Dash Emigrant Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 1 (Xinhua)-- Chinese police have arrested 76
people who were planning to illegally emigrate to the United
States by stowing away on a ship.
</P>
<P>
The group was discovered on the coastal shore of east China's
Fujian Province after failing to make contact with the vessel.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a report from a local tip off, Putian County police
swooped to the area in the early hours of August 31 and found many
of the band walking disconsolately back from the seashore.
</P>
<P>
The police learned that they had tried to reach a big cargo
ship in two fishing boats on the evening of August 30. But when
there was no sign of it at the appointed time they decided to
return home and set out another day.
</P>
<P>
Police confiscated two mini-vans used by the group of people
mostly from counties near Fuzhou, capital of Fujian Province. No
further information on who had organized the plan is available at
this point. The case is still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
