<HEADLINE> China Publishes Veteran's Book On Japanese Invasion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese version of "Japan
's Responsibility for War", a book written by a Japanese veteran
about his country's aggression against China between 1931 and 1945,
went on sale today.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese version was jointly published by the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences (CASS) and the Social Science Document
Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The author of the book, Wakatsuke Yasuo, was recruited into the
Japanese army in the 1930s and later took part in the Japanese
aggression against China. He said he meant the book to be an
atonement for his crimes.
</P>
<P>
In his book, Wakatsuke Yasuo writes that it was the Japanese
militarists who waged the catastrophic war against China which
caused huge miseries for both the Japanese and Chinese people. He
cites the Mikado, or the Emperor of Japan, and the Mikado system
as the chief culprits and criminals who should take the blame for
the war.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese version of this book was issued in Japan in 1995,
creating a great stir among the public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
