The paper said that a mass musical concert, which consists of
cultural dances, mass choir performances, live bands and fireworks
at the Eagle Square, has been proposed for the last day of the
millennium, December 31.
</P>
<P>
As a consequence of the plan, the annual National Festival will
dovetail into the millennium celebration, from December 29 to 31,
with a national costume parade featuring the various dress codes
of the different ethnic groups in the country.
</P>
<P>
Two plays depicting Nigeria's struggle for emancipation against
 colonialism -- Ovonramwen and Attahiru -- will be staged around
the country by the National Troupe, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that a book fair would also be held to showcase
Nigeria' s intellectual achievements in major cities across the
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
