<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Opens Office in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank officially
opened its new Singapore office Wednesday, declaring the objective
of the move is to facilitate the institution's liaison with local
and regional entities, to coordinate the bank's work program and
to develop long-term strategy for the bank in the region.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Permanent Secretary for the Ministry of Finance Lim
Siong Guan and Vice President of the East Asia and Pacific Region
of the World Bank Michel Severino jointly officiated at the
opening of the World Bank office.
</P>
<P>
Severino said at the opening ceremony that the office will
maintain close contacts with official and private sector experts
in Singapore, the financial community in the city state and
elsewhere in the region and regional coordinating bodies and think
tanks.
</P>
<P>
He noted the economic and financial volatility in the region in
the past two years has set back the poverty reduction efforts that
have been promising in this region.
</P>
<P>
"The crisis underlined a fundamental truth: that economic
growth must be sustainable institutionally, socially,
environmentally and culturally," he said.
</P>
<P>
"But we know that this is very difficult to achieve --
especially from a starting point of widespread poverty," he added.
</P>
<P>
Severino emphasized that "the crisis also underlined all
countries, whether rich or poor, must play their part to promote
global prosperity, stability and security."
</P>
<P>
On the functions of the office, Severino said The world Bank is
mandated to assist the poorer countries and the office will help
deepen the World Bank's working relations in Singapore and in the
region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
