<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Application for Macao SAR Legislator Seat Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Office of the
Secretariat of the Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR) began on Wednesday to receive
applications of local residents for a seat that will be available
in the SAR legislature.
</P>
<P>
The applicants must be permanent local residents who are 21
years old or older, and application forms must be turned in by
September 15, according to Tina Ting Yee Ho, vice secretary-
general of the secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Applicants who obtain the nomination of 20 or more members of
the Selection Committee for the First Government of the Macao SAR
can become candidates, Tina said.
</P>
<P>
The future Legislative Council of the Macao SAR will have 23
members, the same as in the current Macao Legislative Assembly.
</P>
<P>
From August 9 to 20, 15 out of the current 16 elected
legislators had requested for continued membership. However, the
seven legislators appointed by the Macao governor cannot extend
their membership after the handover.
</P>
<P>
On August 29, the 10th plenary session of the Preparatory
Committee approved the qualification of the 15 legislators to
become Macao SAR legislators.
</P>
<P>
In this case, one more person has to be selected by the
Selection Committee which consists of 199 members who are all
local residents coming from various social sectors.
</P>
<P>
After the application process is over, candidates will
publicize themselves before Selection Committee members on
September 19. An election will be held on September 20 and the
person who gets the most votes will become SAR legislator, Tina
said.
</P>
<P>
Edmund Ho Hau Wah, chief executive-designate of the Macao SAR,
is expected to appoint seven legislators of the SAR at the end of
this month. And then the SAR legislators will be busy making
necessary preparations for the establishment of the SAR on
December 20 this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
