<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Up 0.45 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks gained 61.
42 points, or 0.45 percent, to close at 13,544.19 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong market opened strongly despite an overnight fall
on the U.S. market, but weakened late in the session. Dealers said
the reason is that investors were worried about the weakness in
the U.S. markets.
</P>
<P>
Market turnover was 5.715 billion HK dollars (732 million U.S.
dollars), 471 million HK dollars (60 million U.S. dollars) less
than Tuesday's turnover of 6.186 billion HK dollars (792 million U.
S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Finance Counter, Utilities, Properties and Commerce and
Industry made across-the-board increases of 0.42 percent, 0.21
percent, 0.96 percent and 0.36 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended with the Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index down 1.46 percent and the Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index down 2.63 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks opened up 78.31 points, or 0.58 percent, at 13,
561.08 Wednesday and closed the morning session at 13,5618.21.
</P>
</TEXT>
