<HEADLINE> New Gas Find Confirmed in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Department of
Energy confirmed Wednesday earlier reports on the discovery of new
gas deposits in the southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
As a support for Philippine President Joseph Estrada's earlier
disclosure of the event, Energy Secretary Mario Tiaoqui said the
gas find in Maguindanao, Mindanao, is of good quality and is
expected to provide ample supply to the local market.
</P>
<P>
He said the gas find was made by the Philippine National Oil
Company (PNOC) Exploration Division which drilled about 1,500 feet
(about 500 meters) where an ample deposit of 95 percent methane
gas was discovered, Philippine News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Methane gas is a common household name because it is used for
cooking and other industrial uses.
</P>
<P>
According to Tiaoqui, the gas find is estimated to have a flow
rate of more than 200,000 cubic feet per day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
