<HEADLINE> One Dead in Clashes in East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Clashes occurred near a U.N.
compound in Dili, capital of East Timor, on Wednesday afternoon,
killing at least one person, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place after hundreds of pro-integration
militia followers attended the funeral of a pro-integration member
killed on Sunday by pro-independence supporters in Dili.
</P>
<P>
CNN reported that around 200 people had taken refuge inside the
U.N. Mission in East Timor (UNAMET) compound after militiamen
fought a running battle with an unidentified group.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that tension returned to East Timor on Tuesday,
one day after a peaceful vote on the territory's future.
</P>
<P>
A group of people armed with homemade guns were seen stopping
motorists heading to the western outskirts of Dili on Tuesday. A
similar scene was reported in Manatuto, some 60 kilometers east of
Dili.
</P>
<P>
The direct ballot on August 30 was to determine whether East
Timor, a former Portuguese colony, will enjoy wide-ranging
autonomy within Indonesia or get independence. East Timor was
integrated into Indonesia in 1976, but the move was never
recognized by the United Nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
