<HEADLINE> Scientists Call for New Development Strategy for Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The development strategy for
northwest China should focus on promoting the overall development
of science, technology, information and education rather than
merely pursuing economic growth, a leading group of Chinese
scientists have declared.
</P>
<P>
In a special report which was released here today, members of
the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), China's top scientific
research organization, proposed a new strategy for the
northwestern region.
</P>
<P>
The scientists share the opinion that the major gaps between
the northwestern and eastern region of China lie in scientific
knowledge, information, education and technology.
</P>
<P>
"And these gaps cannot be narrowed by simply increasing capital
investment and exploring natural resources only," said the report.
</P>
<P>
The consultation report proposes giving priority to narrowing
that particular gaps between the northwestern region and the
developed coastal areas.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin pointed out recently that
accelerating the development in northwest China requires new
thoughts, and that changes in the domestic and international
markets should be taken into full consideration.
</P>
<P>
The scientists suggested that the development of education, the
reform of scientific and technological systems and the
construction of communication facilities should be at the top of
the agenda in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
They also offered advice on issues covering health care,
population, employment, poverty reduction and water resources
utilization along with environmental and ecological protection.
</P>
<P>
"It is the responsibility of CAS academicians to offer advice
on China's major economic and social problems," said Sun Honglie,
a CAS academician, adding that the consultation report will be
submitted to the State Council and related governmental
departments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0187 </DOCNO>
