<HEADLINE> Afghan Opposition Claims Gains in North </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's anti-Taliban
alliance Wednesday claimed making gains in two northern provinces
and inflicting significant losses on the Taliban militia.
</P>
<P>
Opposition commander General Sayed Anwari said alliance troops,
in recent fierce fighting in Jawzjan Province, captured the
strategic town of Alaghan and seized large quantities of
ammunition, armored vehicles and heavy weapons, according to news
reaching here.
</P>
