<HEADLINE> New Indonesian Legislators to Be Installed in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will install the new
members of the House of Representatives (DPR) and the People's
Consultative Assembly (MPR) between October 1 and 3 here, the MPR
General Secretariat announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said the schedule was based on a decision made
by the General Election Commission recently.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the National Election Committee is
scheduled to announce soon the final allocation of the DPR seats
according to the results of the election.
</P>
<P>
Forty-eight political parties took part in the general election
on June 7 this year to compete for 462 of the 500 seats in the
house. The remaining 38 seats are reserved for the military, whose
members do not vote.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI-P) won the
election with 33.74 percent of the votes, outnumbering the ruling
Golkar Party, which trailed with 22.44 percent.
</P>
<P>
The MPR, the country's highest decision-making body, will meet
in November to elect the country's next president. It comprises
the DPR members plus 200 appointed regional and interest groups'
representatives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
