<HEADLINE> Urumqi Trade Fair Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Eighth Urumqi Foreign
Economic and Trade Fair opened in this capital city of northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region today.
</P>
<P>
The number of participants and visitors is expected to reach
more than 5,000, including delegations from Russia, Khazakstan,
Kirghistan, Uzbekistan, Pakistan, the Republic of Korea and Japan,
as well as 39 groups sent by Beijing, Shanghai, Guangdong,
Chongqing, Xinjiang and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment is expected to flow into 77 projects,
covering the sectors of agriculture, light industry, foodstuffs,
chemicals, basic facilities and tourism.
</P>
<P>
The Urumqi trade fair, one of the four largest in China, has
greatly enhanced the economic cooperation between Xinjiang and
foreign business people.
</P>
<P>
The previous seven fairs reported a combined transaction value
of 10.35 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Tomur Dawamat, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Chinese National People's Congress, attended today's opening
ceremony. 
</P>
