<HEADLINE> Iran's FM Departs for Visit to Finland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi left here Wednesday morning for a two-day visit to
Finland, which now holds the rotating presidency of the European
Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Local media said Iran's relations with Finland and the EU will
be high on the agenda of Kharrazi's talks with his Finnish
counterpart.
</P>
<P>
The visit is seen here as part of Iran's effort to woo
European countries. Tehran has normalized relations with EU
members states, which were disrupted by Iran's condemnation of
British writer Salmon Rushdie for his book, The Satanic Verses.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi and Finish officials will discuss issues of mutual
interest as well as key regional and international developments,
according to the Islamic Republic News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Iran hopes to expand and consolidate ties with Finland and the
EU in political, economic and cultural fields, and follow up
signed agreements on mutual cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Finland took over the six-month EU presidency on July 1.
</P>
