<HEADLINE> China Plans to Issue More Treasury Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Finance
announced here today that it will issue 60 billion yuan worth of
treasury bonds to commercial banks on Friday.
</P>
<P>
These T-bonds are not part of the government's original plan at
the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year bonds have floating interest rates, which will
remain 0.3 percentage points above the average interest on savings
deposits for the period. They can be traded on China's inter-bank
bond market but are not available for individual investors.
</P>
<P>
Banks that are backing the bonds include Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China, Agricultural Bank of China, Bank of
China, and Construction Bank of China.  
</P>
