<HEADLINE> Uganda's Former Mayor Jailed in U.S. to Be Freed: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's former mayor of the
capital city Kampala, who is now in a jail in the United States,
would be freed later in September.
</P>
<P>
Nasser Sebaggala, who was sentenced to 15 months' imprisonment
in February for bank fraud, transportation of forged checks and
lying to the United States, would be released on September 23,
Tuesday's New Vision daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Sebaggala was arrested in June of 1998 and convicted later in
Boston, the United States. His conviction and sentence deprived
him of the mayorship automatically according to the Ugandan laws.
</P>
<P>
Though being accused of being short of an A level certificate
required by the top post in the capital city, Sebaggala enjoyed
massive support among the common people. His misfortune was widely
believed to have been the result of some plot.  
</P>
</TEXT>
