<HEADLINE> Australia Set Swimming World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Australia's Michael Klim,
Matthew Dunn, Todd Pearson and Bill Kirby set a short-course world
record in the men's 4x200 meters freestyle relay on Wednesday with
a time of seven minutes and 1.06 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The Australian foursome set the new record in a special time
trial held at the Australian Institute of Sport after seeking
approval from the sport's world governing body FINA.
</P>
<P>
Their time bettered the listed record of 7:02.74 set by Klim,
Dunn, Kirby and Grant Hackett at the 1997 short-course world
championships in Gothenburg, Sweden. 
</P>
