<HEADLINE> Asian Parliamentarians' Conference for Peace and Cooperation Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A four-day conference of Asian
legislators started here Wednesday morning to identify the role of
parliamentarians in creating and promoting an atmosphere of peace
in the region.
</P>
<P>
Law-makers from 33 Asian countries are here to attend the
"Asian Parliamentarians' Conference for Peace and Cooperation,"
initiated by Bangladesh early this year.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-three countries have been invited, and representatives
from 33 countries, including Bangladesh, Cambodia, China,
Indonesia, Malaysia, Pakistan, South Korea, Thailand and Vietnam,
have come to attend the conference funded by the Bangladeshi
government and the United Nations Development Program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0229 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese MP Emphasizes Peace, Development and Cooperation at Asian Parliamentarians' Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- It is still the common
aspiration of the world people and the mainstream of the times to
seek peace, development and cooperation at the time of entering a
new century and a new millennium, a senior Chinese official told a
four-day conference of Asian legislators started here Wednesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Law-makers from 33 Asian countries are here to attend the
"Asian Parliamentarians' Conference for Peace and Cooperation"
initiated by Bangladesh early this year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony on behalf of all the
parliamentary delegations attending the conference, Head of the
Chinese Delegation Zeng Jianhui said the meeting "will promote
mutual understanding and cooperation among parliamentarians and
peoples of various countries and will contribute to regional peace
and development."
</P>
<P>
"Looking back into the 20th century, human society has created
unprecedented material wealth and cultural civilization but also
suffered from two disastrous world wars. The Cold War has been
over, but the issue of peace and development have not been
resolved," said Zeng, who is also chairman of the Foreign Affairs
Committee of China's National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
"Asia takes up over half of the world population. Its stability
and prosperity is a great contribution to world peace and
development," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Hegemonism and power politics have registered new development,
"neo-interventionism" is on the rise while trampling on the norms
of international relations, infringement upon other countries'
sovereignty and interference in the internal affairs of others can
be seen from time to time, the Chinese official observed.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on economic globalization, he said that though
globalization may promote economic growth, "we must not neglect
the fact that the economic globalization process dominated by the
developed countries has intensified unfair international
competitions and brought enormous financial and economic risks to
the developing countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Reality proves that, it is an urgent task for all peace-loving
countries and peoples to uphold the internationally-acknowledged
norms particularly the principles of mutual respect for
sovereignty and territorial integrity, non-aggression,
non-interference in each other's internal affairs, equality and
mutual benefit and peaceful coexistence, and to safeguard the
authority of the United Nations and its role that can not be
replaced, and to promote the establishment of a peaceful and
stable, just and reasonable new international political and
economic order," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"As parliamentarians, we have the responsibility to reflect the
voices of the people and pursue peace and happiness for the
people. We should have the courage to shoulder the duty assigned
to us by history and the people, unite together with one will and
join hands in exploring effective ways and means to maintain peace
and stability in Asia and the world," he added.
</P>
<P>
Participating the conference are 105 members of parliament of
33 Asian countries and 38 members of civil societies of these
countries, including Bangladesh, China, Indonesia, Cambodia,
Indonesia, Malaysia, Pakistan, South Korea, Thailand and Vietnam.
The conference is being funded by the Bangladeshi government and
the United Nations Development Program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
