<HEADLINE> Comets' Chancellor Wins WNBA Coach of Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 31 (Xinhua) -- It's a hat trick for Houston
Comets coach Van Chancellor, although he barely edged Sacramento's
Sonny Allen by one vote for the WNBA Coach of the Year Honors for
the third consecutive year.
</P>
<P>
Chancellor received 18 out of a possible 51 votes from a panel
of sportswriters and broadcasters. Allen finished with 17 votes,
followed by Los Angeles' Orlando Woolridge with 11.
</P>
<P>
Chancellor guided the Comets to a 26-6 record, the best in the
league for the third straight year. They owned the league's best
home and road records at 15-1 and 11-5, respectively, holding
their opponents to a league-low 64.7 points.
</P>
<P>
The Comets will meet the New York Liberty in the WNBA Finals,
beginning Thursday in New York.
</P>
<P>
New York's Richie Adubato received one vote for Coach of the
Year honors.
</P>
<P>
Before Joining the Comets, Chancellor spent 19 seasons as the
women's basketball coach at the University of Mississippi. He led
the Lady Rebels to a 439-154 record, including 14 NCAA Tournament
appearances and nine regional berths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
