<HEADLINE> Poll Shows BJP Alliance Set to Win in Indian Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey shows that
the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) and its allies are poised to gain
an absolute overall majority in the 13th Lok Sabha (lower house)
elections in India.
</P>
<P>
The survey was conducted earlier this month in 76 Lok Sabha
constituencies in 15 states, the Hindustan Times said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The survey, commissioned by the Hindustan Times, was conducted
by ACNielsen, formerly known as MRAS and the world's largest
market research company.
</P>
<P>
The findings are based on interviews with 13,959 voters between
August 14-23.
</P>
<P>
While giving a total of 300 seats to the BJP-led alliance,
called the National Democratic Alliance (NDA), the survey
forecasts a combined tally of 146 for the Congress party and its
regional partners, 20 seats less compared to the 1998 results.
</P>
<P>
Of the 300 seats for the NDA, the BJP is expected to get 190
seats. The Congress itself is likely to win only 123 seats.
</P>
</TEXT>
