<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0253 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Produces Over 4,000 Tons of Cotton Yarn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar produced a total of
4,080 tons of cotton yarn in fiscal 1998-99 which ended in March,
318 tons more than that in the previous year which was 3,762 tons.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figures published by the Central
Statistical Organization, Myanmar also produced 11,895,000 meters
of cotton fabrics in the fiscal year, extending a length of
2,032,215 meters from 9,862,785 meters in the previous fiscal
year.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's annual cultivated area of cotton is 283,500 hectares,
while annual production of cotton stands at over 160,000 tons, of
which long staple cotton accounts for 82 percent.
</P>
<P>
To maintain the enthusiasm of cotton growers and relieve the
shortage of investment capital, the government not only provides
annually more than 1 billion kyats (over 3 million U.S. dollars)
of loans to the growers, but also grants advance payment for the
purchase of cotton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
