<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A total of 492 hotels were in
operation in Myanmar with 13,984 rooms as of March this year,
according to a latest tourism information sheet issued by the
Ministry of Hotels and Tourism.
</P>
<P>
The hotels included 21 foreign-invested, four joint-ventures,
439 local private-owned and 28 state-owned ones.
</P>
<P>
The document also revealed that there were 521 licensed tour
companies in Myanmar as of March this year, which include 508
local companies, 12 joint ventures and a foreign company.
</P>
<P>
It added that a total of 3,768 licensed tour guides were
involved in the period with 2,644 working in English, 486 in
Japanese, 222 in Chinese and 189 in French.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a total of 292,282 foreign tourists visited Myanmar
in fiscal 1998-99 which ended in March, of whom 172,007 came by
land routes through border points, according to other official
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Since Myanmar adopted the open-door market-oriented economic
policy in late 1988, foreign investment in the tourism sector has
amounted to 1.1 billion U.S. dollars. 
