<HEADLINE> High Technology Is Crucial for Beijing Economy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Developing hi-tech industry is the only possible way in the
long run to assure Beijing's sustainable economic growth," Jia
said, adding that his city has issued over 40 regulations and laws,
to improve the environment for the industry.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the sales volume of Zhongguancun, reached 45.1
billion yuan (about 541.2 million U.S. dollars) last year, and its
sales of software products accounted for 43 percent of the nation'
s total.
</P>
<P>
Beijing will continue its efforts to upgrade key technologies
to reach the world's advanced level by the year 2010, as it
strives to make the Zhongguancun Technological Garden one of the
most advanced in the world in the coming decade.
</P>
<P>
The city also will try to maintain the continuous growth of key
industries, including electronics and information, biological
engineering, new pharmaceuticals, new energy sources, and ecology-
friendly industries.
</P>
<P>
The reform of the city's industrial structure and efforts to
attract overseas investment in hi-tech sectors will continue, as
Beijing encourages further cooperation among scientific research
institutions, universities and industries.
</P>
<P>
All this will not be easy, Jia said. However, Beijing will
firmly adhere to the policies of the central government, focusing
on the principle of developing the local economy through science
and technology. 
</P>
