<HEADLINE> New IT Corporation Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The China National Posts and
Telecommunications Industry Corporation (PTIC), another state-
owned giant in the information sector, was established on Tuesday,
according to today's China Securities.
</P>
<P>
The PTIC, under the former Postal and Telecommunications
Ministry and the subsequent Ministry of Information Industry, is a
shareholding company with three different operation mechanisms
including listed companies, state-owned enterprises, and joint
ventures.
</P>
<P>
Through two decades of development, the company has accumulated
sales of 24.8 billion yuan (2.9 billion U.S. dollars), and this
year's sales target is set at 30 billion yuan (3.6 billion U.S.
dollars), according to Zhang Yan'an, deputy general manager of
PTIC.
</P>
<P>
The group's present activities include the development and
production of digital switchboards, construction of cellular
mobile communication systems, and Internet Protocol phone-related
products.  
</P>
