<HEADLINE> Finnish Company Sonera Ready to Launch First WAP Mobile Phone Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Finnish telecommunication
company Sonera is ready for an immediate launch of the world's
first information service for WAP (Wireless Application Protocol)
mobile phones.
</P>
<P>
The first products of WAP mobile phones are expected to be
available on the market within this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition to providing its own services, Sonera will give its
business partners opportunity to offer their services based on
Sonera's WAP concept.
</P>
<P>
Some of its partners, Finnair and CNN Interactive, for example,
presented their WAP-based services at the launch event here of
Sonera's vendor-independent WAP solution.
</P>
<P>
Timo Ahomaki, Sonera's Development Manager, said WAP provides
an excellent platform for new and more interactive service
products.
</P>
<P>
The products presented here have tapped only a tip of the WAP
potential, he said, adding that this is only natural because the
potential and limitations of the new technology are not yet fully
known.
</P>
<P>
Even though WAP offers new business opportunities, the Sonera
company will meanwhile continue developing services for the "
traditional" mobile phones providing only GSM text messaging.
</P>
</TEXT>
