<HEADLINE> Snowstorm Blocks Tunnel Linking Argentina, Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENAS AIRES, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Around 600 loaded trucks
are trapped in the province of Mendoza, in the east of Argentina,
due to a snowstorm which has blocked access to a tunnel which
terminates in Chile, said the authorities on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The area around the "Cristo Redentor" tunnel, has an
accumulation of snow between 1.20 and 1.40 meters deep on the
Chilean side, and the temperature is 6 degrees below zero, said a
police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
According to the source, the tunnel has been blocked since
Sunday when the snowstorm came. 
