<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela Not to Mediate in Colombian Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Hugo
Chavez said on Tuesday that his government would not mediate in
the conflict between Colombia's leftist guerrillas and the
paramilitary rightists.
</P>
<P>
Chavez said: "We have had various talks in various places with
Colombian President Andrez Pastrana about Colombia's internal
problems, but I will not interfere in this matter."
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan president, who will attend the inauguration
ceremony of the Panamanian President Mireya Moscoso, said that he
is prepared to mediate between the two sides to help negotiate an
end to the Colombian civil war.
</P>
<P>
If the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia asked for his
help, he would have the right to talk with them in Venezuela, said
Chavez.
</P>
<P>
He added that he would not recommend measures like those taken
by the National Constitutional Assembly of Panama and other Latin
American countries.
</P>
<P>
Chavez stressed that every country has the right to search for
its own path, and Venezuela has found its own after suffering a
state of chaos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0282 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> A Chinese Breeder' s Dream (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li found out through later experiments that the close-sowed and
photosynthesis efficient hybrid maize seed is crucial for high
yield, and the results of his first research in this field, called
"No. 2 Yedan", meant he was able to increase the production per
hectare to more than 11.25 tons.
</P>
<P>
Then he decided to move to Sanya City in south China's Hainan
Province for his research work as the comparatively low
temperature in northern China hindered the breeding program's
progress.
</P>
<P>
Over his 21 years of research, he says, he was never bothered by
the mosquitoes and snakes, or the heat. And some dozens of disease
resistant maize species have been formed during the period.
</P>
<P>
His "Yedan" series of hybrid seeds were spread to 28 provinces,
municipalities, and autonomous regions in 1997, the total sowing
acreage accounting for 43.5 percent of the nation's total, and the
economic returns reaching around 50 billion yuan (about 6 billion
U.S. dollars), according to Ministry of Agriculture statistics.
</P>
<P>
"Increasing the annual maize output from 100 million tons to
some 500 million tons in the past 50 years despite farmland
reduction, population increase, and frequent natural adversities,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
"However, it is far from enough, as there are still some 40
million needy people across the country," he added.
</P>
<P>
Together with his colleagues, he set up some 16,700 hectares of
maize breeding bases nationwide last year, planning to double the
size by the year 2000 and increase the use of high-quality maize
seeds to 100,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
"I will work for the agricultural cause of my motherland until
the last breath of my life," he said.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that China has increased its annual crop production
by over 180 million tons in the past four years, while the demand
for the grains has increased by just some 50 million tons.
</P>
<P>
This means, says Li proudly, that China will be able to produce
enough grain to feed its people.
</P>
<P>
It won't be a problem at any time for China to ensure food
security for its people, said officials with the Beijing Office of
the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization.
</P>
<P>
China still has an idle land of 35 million hectares suitable
for agricultural undertakings, and 14.7 million hectares of which
may be used for grain production.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
