<HEADLINE> Korda Banned for One Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Former Australian Open champion
Petr Korda lost an arbitration ruling in Lausanne Tuesday and
received a one-year-ban until August 31, 2000 for testing positive
for the steroid Nandrolone at Wimbledon last year.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Czech star was ordered to forfeit all prize
money earned since July 1998.
</P>
<P>
The ruling by the Court of Arbitration for Sport ends a
protracted legal battle between Korda and the International Tennis
Federation.
</P>
<P>
The CAS ruled there were no "exceptional circumstances" that
would excuse Korda from any suspension. 
</P>
</TEXT>
