<HEADLINE> Explosion Leaves Five Dead in Havana Shipyard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Five workers were killed and four
others injured when an oxygen tank exploded in the Havana military
shipyard, said the Ministry of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of
Cuba (MINFAR) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred on Monday afternoon when workers were
repairing a floating jetty in the shipyard of the Industrial
Military Company Granma, east of Havana, confirmed MINFAR.
</P>
<P>
The oxygen tank was being used for cutting metal.
</P>
<P>
The authorities said that the investigation into the accident
is going on. 
</P>
