<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index of
the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange went up 1.17 percent to 506.71
points on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Merval index rose 6.53 percent by the end of August,
compared with the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 21.802 million U.S. dollars against 12.38
million dollars on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The annual interbank rate of interest stood at 5.65 percent in
the 24-hour term. The parity of the peso against the dollar
remained unchanged at 0.997 for purchase and 1.002 for sale.
</P>
</TEXT>
