<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0295 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Finds New Gene Causing Hereditary Deafness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Italian medical researchers found a
new gene playing a role in hereditary deafness, a problem that
affects one person out of every 2,000 and which is the cause of at
least half of the hearing defects found in newborns.
</P>
<P>
According to the Italian news agency Ansa, the new gene,
"connexina 30," was found in humans by Italians Paolo Gasparini
and Leopoldo Zelante, researchers in the field of genetics at the
hospital in Italy's southern province of Foggia.
</P>
<P>
The discovery is yet another step forward in the precocious
diagnosis of hereditary deafness and efforts to combat
deaf-mutism.
</P>
<P>
The gene had already been found in laboratory rats. The
Italians managed to isolate it and then, through the study of some
200 families suffering from hereditary deafness, to find the same
gene in humans.
</P>
<P>
They further discovered that a mutation in "connexina 30" had
rendered the protein the gene produces incapable of letting
electric charges pass to neighboring cells.
</P>
<P>
There are around 60 genes suspected of involvement in
hereditary deafness. Around 12 of them have been shown to play a
part while the worst of them, "connexina 26," was discovered two
years ago, also in Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0296 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Fair of Inventions, New Technologies Opens In U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The China Fair of Inventions
and New Technologies, the first of its kind held in the U.S.,
opened at the Washington Convention Center here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, Guo Xiaodong, deputy commissioner of
the State Intellectual Property Office of China, said the Chinese
government attaches great importance to the protection of
intellectual property.
</P>
<P>
"China's patent system, which was established during the
country's reform and opening up, has scored a significant
achievement," Guo said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May, the total amount of patent applications
filed in China has exceeded 910,000. The amount of granted patents
is over 460,000. Of the total amount of patent applications, 16
percent are from foreign countries including the U.S.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the fair will further promote the
understanding and cooperation between the U.S. and China in the
field of intellectual property.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the same ceremony, Todd Dickinson, acting assistant
secretary of commerce and acting commissioner of patent and
trademarks, said the U.S. and China have enjoyed a good working
relationship for a number of years in the area of intellectual
property.
</P>
<P>
"We know that China is in the process of amending some of its
intellectual property laws, such as the copyright and trademark
laws, and we look forward to seeing these laws fully implemented
to provide all intellectual property owners greater protection
for their intellectual efforts," he said.
</P>
<P>
The three-day fair, co-sponsored by the State Intellectual
Property Office of China and the U.S.-China Council for
International Exchange, Inc., is being held to exhibit China's
intellectual property protection system and its accomplishments as
well as to promote better understanding and cooperation between
the U.S. and China in the intellectual property area.
</P>
<P>
On display are over 200 Chinese inventions and new technologies
which have been patented in China, including consumer electronics,
gardening, health and medical care, environmental protection
technology and industrial machinery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
