<HEADLINE> Congolese Rebel Leader Hails Signing of Peace Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A Congolese rebel faction leader
Ernest Wamba Dia Wamba Tuesday described the signing of a peace
agreement as the " first phase for the Congolese people to move
for peace".
</P>
<P>
Wamba Dia Wamba, leader of the group of the Congolese Rally for
 Democracy (RCD), made these remarks at a press conference after
the signing of the peace agreement by 46 founding members of the
main rebel group in Lusaka Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his satisfaction with the signing of the document
and also called on African countries to help the Democratic
Republic of the Congo (DRC) get democracy and become politically
stable.
</P>
<P>
He said it is a relief, an encouragement and also a great hope
that southern Africa has completed its process of reversal of a
bitter history in its relation to the eternal suffering of the
Congo.
</P>
<P>
With this regional oath, the rebel leader said: "We have shown
that we africans are now politically mature."
</P>
<P>
He also urged the international community and the United
Nations to continue supporting the Congolese people for finding a
lasting peace through political talks in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
