<DOCNO> XIE19990901.0303 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Tuesday with blue chip stocks falling and technology shares
rising.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 84.85 at 10,829.28
for the fourth consecutive sessions. The index fell 452.91 points
in the three previous tradings.
</P>
<P>
But the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 26.66 at
2,739.35. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index fell 3.61 at 1,320.41.
</P>
<P>
The Dow moved lower as investors were concerned about inflation
after the National Association of Purchasing Management released
inadvertently one day ahead of schedule the August survey on
manufacturing activity. The survey showed growth in the industrial
sector of the U.S. economy, indicating the build-up of
inflationary pressures.
</P>
<P>
The increase in inflationary pressures would convince investors
that the Federal Reserve would raise interest rates for the third
time this year. The Federal Reserve raised interest rates twice in
the past two months in a bid to preempt inflation from the U.S.
economy.
</P>
<P>
The technology shares rose on the merger. Sun Microsystems
acquired Star Division Corp., a small maker of office productivity
software and the acquisition was seen as an assault on Microsoft's
dominance of the office software market.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 2.80 at 612.33. But the American Stock
Exchange index rose 0.20 at 775.41 and the Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 0.47 at 427.83.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 5-to-4 margin, on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,671 down, 1,316 up and 582
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 838.40 million shares from 585.59
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
